For Demo Downloaders:
---------------------

Once you've unzipped to the directory of your choice,
run SETSOUND to configure your sound setup, and then run
ASCEND to run Ascendancy. If Ascendancy tells you it can't find a
VESA driver, type "uvconfig -gen" to configure the UNIVBE driver.
That's all!


Ascendancy Demo README File
---------------------------


This file contains:

1.  A list of what game features are absent from this demo.
2.  A list of special keyboard commands that can be used during the demo.
3.  A list of files installed to your hard drive.
4.  Machine Requirements & Technical Tips
5.  Ways to contact The Logic Factory for more information.

Enjoy!


1. Features NOT included in this demo      
-------------------------------------

* Cinematic introduction
* Full tutorial system, explaining all aspects of the game
* 21 unique alien species (only 7 included in this demo)
* Larger galaxy sizes - up to 100 stars
* More opponents per game
* Most of the digital soundtrack, including a theme for each species
* Full access to research tree (demo limits research)
* No limit on # of game days (obviously!)
* A variety of other features and details


2. Special Keyboard Commands
----------------------------

<->         decrease rotate speeds
<+>         increase rotate speeds
<M>         toggle research and planet self-management
<alt-S>     save game
<alt-L>     load game
<alt-M>     toggle music
<alt-N>     toggle sound effects
<alt-X>     exit game


3. Demo Files Installed
-----------------------

20 files occupying approximately 11 megabytes are installed to your hard 
drive in the directory you specified during installation.  To uninstall
the demo, delete these files from your hard drive (or use the DELTREE
command on the directory you installed to):

